Summary

The paranormal had been a long going genre since the first lectures of folk tales of witches to present day screenings of our nightmares. Its whats in the dark that scares us, the simplicity of never knowing that ties well into horror movies of a modern age.

To what extent to fantasize about Sci-Fi movies? Not a very long one, the what if is very limited because it's usually based in a futuristic time that many of us can't relate to. Since it also has very high production value, the jump scares aren't raw to the audience. I wonder how they made that alien? Such things can distract are during the movie rather than a paranormal movie where the scares use small cinema tricks and can create a more realistic tone where many feel they are in the movie
